bibdata.title: alma sandbox incremental publishing job did not create an event in bidata-staging

comments.body: I've checked sqs poller , redis and sidekiq in bibdata-staging. everything is active and running . I also restarted them. I checked the last incremental file in `deploy@bibdata-alma-worker-staging1:~$ ls -lrt /data/marc_liberation_files/` is from March 4th 2022. This is before the database migration on March 15th, 2022. I'm now looking for SQS logs.
This issue is related to https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/3038.

Using `deploy@bibdata-alma-worker-staging1:` I tested indexing a single file using the rake task liberate:index_file as:
`SET_URL=http://lib-solr8-staging.princeton.edu:8983/solr/catalog-staging FILE=/home/deploy/second_file.xml bundle exec rake liberate:index_file` and records were indexed.
I'm also looking into https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/issues/1855 to make sure incremental dumps will be created in bibdata-staging (unrelated so far to rails 6 upgrade) and indexed.

Might want to add https://pod.stanford.edu/ -- I saw that @maxkadel hasn't been added yet.

Here is some documentation from POD: https://github.com/pod4lib/aggregator/wiki/Organization-owner's-manual#users-tab

openpublishing.title: Hashtag/text errors while in Japanese mode

comments.body:
This is due to the fact that there are terms missing from the Japanese language translation files associated with OJS.  

According to documentation, OJS language translations are entirely community-created and many of them are partially incomplete.  A list of languages supported in the program and their completeness of translation can be seen here - 

https://translate.pkp.sfu.ca/projects/ojs/#languages

PKP is very grateful for help making translations more complete; here is the page on their website detailing where and how translations can be contributed to the project - https://pkp.sfu.ca/contributors/translation/ 

If there is bandwidth for this, I would suggest that the Japanese language translation for OJS be expanded and contributed back to the project.  In the short term to remove the visible error, the menu itself could be updated to remove the "Announcements" page in favor of a different link if desired.  

I'm happy to discuss the path forward further and/or demo what I saw investigating this!
